article.headline: Jackson State 81, Southeastern Louisiana 73
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Jackson State's Trey Johnson scored a game-high 33 points to lead three players in double figures as the Tigers built a 13-point halftime lead and held off Southeastern Louisiana 81-73 on Tuesday. Johnson, the nation's leading scorer at 30.0 points entering the game, went 13-for-22 from the floor and scored 19 points in the first half as JSU (4-4) won its fourth straight game. Catraiva Givens added 13 points and four assists for JSU, which shot 59 percent from the floor, including 19-of-23 in the first half. Julius Young added 11 points for the Tigers. Quennell Green led Southeastern (4-2) with 21 points while Daryl Cohen finished with 19. The Lions shot just 38 percent for the game.
